title: arya + babies
body:
She wanted to tease Bran and play with baby Rickon and have Robb smile at her.

She used to throw snowballs at them and help them steal pies from the kitchen. Their wives gave her scones and she invented names for their babies and played monsters-and-maidens and hide-the-treasure and come-into-my-castle with their children.

Baby Bran had clutched at Arya’s hand. […] “You stupid,” she told him, “you scared the baby,” but Jon and Robb just laughed and laughed, and pretty soon Bran and Arya were laughing too.

The Weasel put her arms around her leg, clutching tight. Sometimes she did that now. […] “You leave Weasel alone, she’s just scared and hungry is all.” […] “Quiet,” she told them, putting an arm around Weasel when the little girl came running up.

summary: I miss Arya. Like seriously miss her. I finished reading the books so long ago and now, Winds of Winter is taking so long. I...
body:
I miss Arya. Like seriously miss her. I finished reading the books so long ago and now, Winds of Winter is taking so long. I miss getting excited about her chapters, and desperately trying to keep myself from skipping to her chapters (guilty, very guilty.) I miss my little boo, and her missing her brother, and her getting so sad yet being so brave, and getting all excited about making and talking to her friends. Freaking precious. I miss my little Arry so much.

George R.R. Martin! Where you at?!

summary: Needle was Robb and Bran and Rickon, her mother and her father, even Sansa. Needle was Winterfell’s grey walls, and the laughter...
caption: Needle was Robb and Bran and Rickon, her mother and her father, even Sansa. Needle was Winterfell’s grey walls, and the laughter of its people. Needle was the summer snows, Old Nan’s stories, the heart tree with its red leaves and scary face, the warm earthy smell of the glass gardens, the sound of the north wind rattling the shutters of her room. Needle was Jon Snow’s smile. The Many-Faced God can have the rest, Arya thought, but he can’t have this.

summary: Do you think Cat will get some positive (if that's the right word?) closure in the end? Given how she's spent the entire series...
question: Do you think Cat will get some positive (if that's the right word?) closure in the end? Given how she's spent the entire series with things going bad to worse it'd be nice if she ended up at least with *something* good
answer: Yes, I think Catelyn will eventually rest peacefully. At the very least, I think she encounters Arya; hopefully by that point Arya will be able to tell her that any or all of Sansa, Bran, and Rickon are alive and/or headed towards Winterfell.

summary: Dany fans: Can you please not reduce Dany to a violent, power hungry, merciless mad queen? Also Dany fans: We love our murder...
body:
Dany fans: Can you please not reduce Dany to a violent, power hungry, merciless mad queen?

Also Dany fans: We love our murder baby Arya!

It’s bad enough that Jonsa/Sansa fans reduce Arya to a killer whose only purpose in the story is be Sansa’s bodyguard and kill people for her. Do we need Dany fans doing the same? Especially when their fave has also been reduced to a one-dimensional evil queen by these same fans?

I know it’s the show’s writing to blame but I am tired of all the idiot Jon and killer Arya jokes on their tag.

Hopefully, starting with the Arya-Jon reunion, the show adds more meat to her story than just her going around killing people. Maisie Williams has hinted that we will see a different Arya next season:

“For a lot of the previous season her emotions were very cut off, she just didn’t want to hear what her family had been through,” she told The Times.

“I hope in the new season I get a chance to bring back a bit more of that fun child that we fell in love with.”

Killing is hard for Arya. Like it is for Jon. It has turned Arya into a traumatized child soldier. The point of her story is her slowly withdrawing from killing people and returning to the old Arya of Winterfell. As per Maisie, hopefully we start seeing that Arya next season and her own story in the series.

title: talk between sisters
body:
Two figures were walking into the godswood, silently holding hands and being as close as they could be. They had suffered too much alone to be parted now. Once they were at the Weirwood, they sat down and rested, heads close together.

It was only then that Arya broke her silence. “He’s not worthy of you.” 

“Perhaps, but he is honest and true.” Sansa answered quietly.

“Yes. Maybe. He is strange and I don’t like him. Didn’t like him back then, don’t like him now. You could do with a better match.”

“Yes, I could. Once I thought I had the perfect match, and it was all a lie. The other would have been a good match, but his family proved false. Other could have been our cousin, the last one didn’t care for me at all until he knew my name.”

Arya sighed, “There are still men from the North, the Riverlands even… Edric Dayne would be good.”

“Most men of the North forgot me. Same with those from the Riverlands. I trust your judgement on Lord Dayne, but Dorne is so very far away.”

“And still you pick the mutt.” Arya’s voice was rueful. “Of all people in the world to pick… you went with him. Why?”

“Because he wants me. He wants Sansa, not Lady Stark. Not the Lady of Winterfell, just plain Sansa. Do you understand?”

Arya shook her head, making Sansa sit straight and rest her head on the trunk. “I do. That doesn’t mean I have to like it.”

“Of course you don’t.” Sansa smiled at her sister. “Do I have your support?”

“You do.” Arya gave her solemn nod. “I am sure Bran and Jon will side with you. Rickon -that traitor- likes your mutt well enough.”

“Thank you.” Sansa reached for Arya’s hand, who took it. “I’m glad you’re by my side.”

“You have skills I lack. And I have ones you don’t. More importantly we’re Starks. As father once said to me, we need each other.”

Sansa’s eyes grew wet, her voice shaking a little, “I love you.”

“I love you too.” Arya’s voice was firm and clear. “But… if that mutt so much as looks at you the wrong way, he’ll became an eunuch.”

Sansa laughed, “Sandor has learned his lessons. He’s a changed man. Still, you have my permission to tell him that to his face.”

“Good, because I will. After all, what is family for?”

“Thank you.” Sansa reached for Arya’s hand, who took it. “I’m glad you’re by my side.”

“You have skills I lack. And I have ones you don’t. More importantly we’re Starks. As father once said to me, we need each other.”

Sansa’s eyes grew wet, her voice shaking a little, “I love you.”

“I love you too.” Arya’s voice was firm and clear. “But… if that mutt so much as looks at you the wrong way, he’ll became an eunuch.”

Sansa laughed, “Sandor has learned his lessons. He’s a changed man. Still, you have my permission to tell him that to his face.”

“Good, because I will. After all, what is family for?”
trail.content:
Two figures were walking into the godswood, silently holding hands and being as close as they could be. They had suffered too much alone to be parted now. Once they were at the Weirwood, they sat down and rested, heads close together.

It was only then that Arya broke her silence. “He’s not worthy of you.” 

“Perhaps, but he is honest and true.” Sansa answered quietly.

“Yes. Maybe. He is strange and I don’t like him. Didn’t like him back then, don’t like him now. You could do with a better match.”

“Yes, I could. Once I thought I had the perfect match, and it was all a lie. The other would have been a good match, but his family proved false. Other could have been our cousin, the last one didn’t care for me at all until he knew my name.”

Arya sighed, “There are still men from the North, the Riverlands even… Edric Dayne would be good.”

“Most men of the North forgot me. Same with those from the Riverlands. I trust your judgement on Lord Dayne, but Dorne is so very far away.”

“And still you pick the mutt.” Arya’s voice was rueful. “Of all people in the world to pick… you went with him. Why?”

“Because he wants me. He wants Sansa, not Lady Stark. Not the Lady of Winterfell, just plain Sansa. Do you understand?”

Arya shook her head, making Sansa sit straight and rest her head on the trunk. “I do. That doesn’t mean I have to like it.”

“Of course you don’t.” Sansa smiled at her sister. “Do I have your support?”

“You do.” Arya gave her solemn nod. “I am sure Bran and Jon will side with you. Rickon -that traitor- likes your mutt well enough.”

“Thank you.” Sansa reached for Arya’s hand, who took it. “I’m glad you’re by my side.”

“You have skills I lack. And I have ones you don’t. More importantly we’re Starks. As father once said to me, we need each other.”

Sansa’s eyes grew wet, her voice shaking a little, “I love you.”

“I love you too.” Arya’s voice was firm and clear. “But… if that mutt so much as looks at you the wrong way, he’ll became an eunuch.”

Sansa laughed, “Sandor has learned his lessons. He’s a changed man. Still, you have my permission to tell him that to his face.”

“Good, because I will. After all, what is family for?”
